🔥 2️⃣ How to Prevent Duplicate URLs?
Problem: Same long URL shortened multiple times → storage waste.

✅ Option 1 — Unique Constraint on long_url
Add:
UNIQUE INDEX on long_url
Flow:
Check if URL exists
If yes → return existing short code
If no → create new

⚠ Problem
Checking DB every time adds latency.
✅ Better Approach — Hash-Based Lookup
Store:
long_url_hash → short_code
Flow:
Compute SHA-256 hash of long URL
Check hash index
Return existing mapping if present
Fast and scalable.

🎤 Interview Answer
“I’d maintain a unique index on long_url or its hash.
During creation, I first check existence.
If found, I return existing short URL instead of creating duplicate.”

