🔥 PART 1 — SQL vs NoSQL for URL Shortener
🧠 What Are We Storing?
Core data:

short_code → long_url
Characteristics:
Simple key-value mapping
Read-heavy
Massive scale
Minimal joins

🟢 Option 1 — SQL (MySQL / PostgreSQL)
Pros
Strong consistency (ACID)
Easy uniqueness constraint
Mature indexing
Good for small-medium scale
Easy duplicate prevention

Cons
Vertical scaling limits
Sharding complexity
Write bottlenecks if not designed well

When SQL is Ideal
Moderate scale (< billions)
Need strict consistency
Team familiar with RDBMS

🔵 Option 2 — NoSQL (Cassandra / DynamoDB)
Pros
Horizontal scaling built-in
High write throughput
Designed for key-value lookups
Automatic partitioning

Cons
Eventual consistency (configurable)
Harder duplicate prevention
Limited querying flexibility

